Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_verilog(25.10)                                        init_verilog(25.10)

Name
       init_verilog

Syntax
        init_verilog <list_of_netlist_files>

       Type: String

       Default: NULL

       Specifies  the  gate-level Verilog netlist files to be read. This vari-
       able replaces the  previous  rda_Input(ui_netlist)  configuration  file
       variable.

       An  encrypted Verilog file is allowed to be specified for init_verilog.
       The file can be created by command encrypt -verilog. To be loaded,  the
       encrypted Verilog must have suffix ".vp", like mydesign.vp.

Example
              * The following command specifies z650n3_n2n.enc.dat/z650n3.v as
                the gate-level Verilog netlist file.

                set init_verilog {z650n3_n2n.enc.dat/z650n3.v}

Related Information
              * encrypt

              * init_design

